# 14. Longest Common Prefix

## ğŸ” Intuition
- Compare characters column-wise (vertically)
- Stop when mismatch occurs

---

## ğŸ§  Approach (Vertical Scanning)
- Take first string as reference
- Compare each character with same index in other strings
- If mismatch â†’ return prefix so far

---
## complexity
Time: O(n * m) ,
Space: O(1)
## âœ… Python Code

```python
class Solution:
    def longestCommonPrefix(self, strs: List[str]) -> str:
        if not strs:
            return ""

        shortest = min(strs, key=len)

        for i in range(len(shortest)):
            for string in strs:
                if string[i] != shortest[i]:
                    return shortest[:i]

        return shortest     
